app-run - Compile and run shell scripts

USAGE:
    app-run <file-to-run> [args...]

DESCRIPTION:
    Compile and run a shell script file. The script is built
    using the app build system and executed in a temporary
    environment.

ARGUMENTS:
    file-to-run
        The shell script file to compile and run (required)

CONFIGURATION:
    -conf-install-step-timeout SECONDS
        Timeout per build step (default: 300)

    -conf-install-max-concurrent-jobs NUM
        Maximum concurrent jobs (default: nproc)

    -conf-install-checksum-cmd CMD
        Checksum command (default: "sha256 -q")

EXAMPLES:
    app-run my-script.sh
    app-run test.sh arg1 arg2
